        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 4:53PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Honey Island, or 17 miles west of Leland, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Waccamaw, Makatoka, Hallsboro, Freeman, Honey Island, Redbug,
Exum, Crusoe Island, Brunswick, and Bolton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.</instruction>
